          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Fuel Cell Tax Extenders Act of 2015 </strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to extend through 2021:</p> <ul> <li>the residential energy efficient property tax credit for qualified fuel cell property,</li> <li> the energy tax credit for qualified fuel cell property,</li> <li>the alternative motor vehicle tax credit for qualified fuel cell motor vehicles,</li> <li>the tax credit for alternative fuel vehicle refueling property relating to hydrogen, and </li> <li>the excise tax credit for the sale or use of alternative fuels involving hydrogen. </li> </ul>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
